gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 119, Kings 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns, down as much as 22 points, used a 32-8 run in the final eight minutes of the game to rally back and defeat the Kings, 119-117.  Grayson Allen led the Suns with 29 points, five rebounds, six assists and nine 3PM, while Kevin Durant (27 points (15 in the 4th), five rebounds, four assists) and Devin Booker (16 points, 11 assists) combined for 43 points in the victory.  DeAaron Fox tallied 33 points, six assists and six 3PM for the Kings, while Domantas Sabonis (21 points, 12 rebounds, 11 assists) added his 11th triple-double of the season and 43rd of his career, tied for 11th most all-time with Fat Lever in the losing effort.  The Suns improve to 22-18 on the season, while the Kings fall to 23-17.
